==English==
===Etymology===
Via Latin from the Greek [[ναφθα]] or [[ναφθος]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'næfθə/

===Noun===
'''naphtha'''
# ''(historic)'' naturally-occuring [[liquid]] [[petroleum]]
# any of a wide variety of [[aliphatic]] or [[aromatic]] liquid [[hydrocarbon]] mixtures distilled from [[petroleum]] or [[coal tar]], especially as used in [[solvent]]s or [[petrol]]
#:*'''1995''': The Common Room and the Library were lit by anbaric light, but the Scholars preferred the older, softer '''naphtha''' lamps in the Retiring Room. — Philip Pullman, ''Northern Lights''

